(- Core Terms \(plain language + jargon\)) Tj
T*
(- **Entropy**: random bytes the wallet generates first.) Tj
T*
(- **Checksum bits**: short hash-derived bits added to entropy to catch typing mistakes.) Tj
T*
(- **Mnemonic**: human-readable word list encoding entropy + checksum.) Tj
T*
(- **Seed**: 64-byte root secret derived from mnemonic using PBKDF2.) Tj
T*
(- **PBKDF2**: password-based key derivation function. Slows down brute-force attacks.) Tj
T*
(- **HKDF**: key expansion method with context labels so different branches are separated.) Tj
T*
(- **Falcon**: post-quantum signature scheme \(identity + signing\).) Tj
T*
(- **Kyber**: post-quantum KEM/encryption key agreement \(private payload lock/unlock\).) Tj
T*
(- **HPK**: hashed public key digest \(role/network-domain hashed Falcon pubkey\).) Tj
T*
(- **Base56**: human-oriented encoding alphabet with typo-resistant rules.) Tj
T*
(- **Private bundle**: binary package that contains Falcon public key + Kyber public key.) Tj
T*
(- **X-hash / X-address**: hash-based identifier for private bundle sharing.) Tj
T*
(- **Note**: private spendable object \(private UTXO-like record\).) Tj
T*
(- **Nullifier**: one-time spend marker that prevents private double-spend.) Tj
T*
(- **Anchor/Merkle path**: proof that a note exists in the private note tree.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
