(Q1\) Is mnemonic generated from seed?) Tj
T*
(No. In this implementation, entropy is generated first, mnemonic is encoded from) Tj
T*
(entropy+checksum, then seed is derived from mnemonic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q2\) Why can two wallets with same words look different?) Tj
T*
(Common reasons:) Tj
T*
(- different passphrase,) Tj
T*
(- different account/index/role path,) Tj
T*
(- different network.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q3\) Why are Falcon and Kyber both needed?) Tj
T*
(Falcon signs ownership and spend intent. Kyber encrypts private payload exchange for note) Tj
T*
(delivery/decode.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q4\) Why not one key type for everything?) Tj
T*
(Separation reduces cross-protocol risk and keeps concerns cleaner: signing vs encapsulation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q5\) Is address checksum optional?) Tj
T*
(No. It is integral for typo detection and safe sharing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q6\) Why Base56 instead of hex everywhere?) Tj
T*
(Base56 is shorter, more human-friendly, and avoids visually ambiguous characters.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q7\) If I lose local key JSON, can mnemonic recover me?) Tj
T*
(Yes for deterministic key identity and confirmed on-chain state, after full sync/rescan.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q8\) Will pending mempool items always recover?) Tj
T*
(Not guaranteed as local transient state. They are resolved by eventual chain inclusion or drop.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q9\) Why does private send sometimes require shielding first?) Tj
T*
(If you do not have enough confirmed private note balance, wallet may need public -> private-self) Tj
T*
(first.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q10\) Does private sending hide everything?) Tj
T*
(Private outputs are hidden as commitments, but flow design still matters. Public legs are public) Tj
T*
(by definition.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q11\) Why is role separation important?) Tj
T*
(It prevents one role identity from being accidentally reused as another role in policy-sensitive) Tj
T*
(logic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q12\) Can deterministic keys still be secure?) Tj
T*
(Yes, if root seed is secret and derivation is domain-separated and cryptographically strong.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q13\) What if attacker sees my public address?) Tj
T*
(Public address alone does not reveal private key. It is derived from hashed pubkey and protected) Tj
T*
(by signature hardness assumptions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q14\) What if attacker sees my X-address?) Tj
T*
(X-address is an identifier from bundle hash, not your private secret itself.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q15\) Why are some private tx payload fields large?) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
