(Q16\) What prevents private double-spend?) Tj
T*
(Nullifier uniqueness checks plus proof/signature validation in mempool and block validation) Tj
T*
(paths.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q17\) What prevents fake note minting?) Tj
T*
(Amount/commit/proof validation and consensus rules. Inputs and outputs must satisfy protocol) Tj
T*
(constraints.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q18\) Is wallet UI balance always authoritative?) Tj
T*
(UI is a view. Consensus-confirmed chain state is authoritative.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q19\) Why do notes move pending -> spendable?) Tj
T*
(Confirmation policy exists to avoid spendability on unstable/unconfirmed state.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q20\) Why does passphrase matter so much?) Tj
T*
(Passphrase changes PBKDF2 salt input. Same words + different passphrase = completely different) Tj
T*
(seed and keys.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q21\) Can I share mnemonic to support staff?) Tj
T*
(Never. Mnemonic + passphrase controls your entire deterministic wallet tree.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q22\) Why store notes in a separate notes JSON too?) Tj
T*
(Operational/audit clarity and faster reconciliation workflows, while canonical spend truth) Tj
T*
(remains consensus.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q23\) If chain is wiped and restarted, should old spendable notes still show?) Tj
T*
(No. Proper rescan/reconciliation should self-heal against current chain state.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q24\) Why does code enforce integer atoms?) Tj
T*
(Integer atoms avoid floating-point rounding errors in monetary accounting.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Q25\) What is the single most important backup set?) Tj
T*
(Mnemonic phrase, passphrase \(if used\), and derivation path metadata. Then run full node) Tj
T*
(sync/rescan.) Tj
